[thinking] **Examining JDK Throwable rules**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about how JDK's Throwable class works, specifically regarding the private transient Throwable cause and synchronized initCause methods. Since setCause is package-private and final, a subclass can't define a method with the same signature because it's final. But, I'm wondering if package-private means that it's inherited. The JLS says you can't override methods that aren't accessible. So, if the subclass has a method with the same signature as a non-private method, it overrides—but I think package-private methods in a different package aren't inherited or overridden.
